<br>
Elemental and magic damage ratings work similaly, but the mob gets a resist check versus the bonus damage, unlike bane weapons who always add the damage rating versus the specified mobs.<br>
<br>
So a 14/24 one hander with 10 Fire damage would hit a mob, do a resist check and if the mob failed would be 14/24 with an added simultaneous 10 damage attack in the same swing using the same attack value as the swing itself to determine damage. <br>
<br>
Off hand elemental and magic weapons have been reported to hit for 2 minimum leading to this theory of combat resolution. Bane weapons on the other hand have not had such reports when used off hand.<br>
<br>
These are still mostly speculation on how EXACTLY they work, but this guide shoudl be pretty accurate. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105286">Gilfalas Elaandrin</a>, Lvl 59 Knight of Tunare & Defender of Nature<br>
