like swinging a 14/24 and 10/24 at the same time and adding the damage together. Which gives the 2 on offhand min.<br>
hmmm. And it would be reasonably easy to code that way, just put them both on the same swing timer and add the results at the end.<br>
Throw the damage calculated by your elemental 10/24 portion of the weapon through a resist check to see how much you add to the other part of the weapon.<br>
Makes sense.<br>
I was trying to figure out how they would calculate it, this seems to be a pretty reasonable solution.<br>
